The paper deals with the computational complexity of the Feedback Vertex Set problem, which is a classic problem in graph theory and is relevant to many areas of computer science. The paper specifically focuses on the parameterization of the problem by mim-width, which is a measure of the complexity of a graph decomposition. This makes it likely that the paper would be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper involves graph theory and combinatorics, which could lead to classification under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper involves the construction of a new gadget, which could lead to classification under cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
